  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Storeman",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We are looking for a skilled and reliable <strong>Storeman </strong>to join our kitchen team. The storeman job responsibilities are:<br /><br /><strong>Inventory & Stock Control</strong></p><ul><li>Receive and check incoming goods against delivery orders and invoices.</li><li>Verify quantity, quality, expiry dates, and packaging condition.</li><li>Record stock movement accurately in inventory system or stock cards.</li><li>Maintain FIFO / FEFO practices for all food items.</li><li>Conduct regular stock counts and assist in monthly stock take.</li><li>Any other work duties assigned by superior. </li></ul><p><strong>Storage & Handling</strong></p><ul><li>Storw raw materials, ingredients, and packaging correctly in dry, chiller, or freezer areas.</li><li>Ensure proper labelling, segregation, and cleanliness of storage areas.</li><li>Monitor temperature and storage conditions according to food safety requirements.</li><li>Maintain good housekeeping and hygiene standards at all times.</li></ul><p><strong>Issuance & Coordination</strong></p><ul><li>Issue ingredients and supplies to kitchen production based on requisitions.</li><li>Coordinate with kitchen, procurement, and QA teams on stock availability.</li><li>Flag low stock levels, discrepancies, damages, or expired items promptly.</li></ul><p><strong>Food Safety & Compliance</strong></p><ul><li>Comply with SFA / HACCP / ISO / internal food safety standards.</li><li>Follow pest control, hygiene, and sanitation procedures.</li><li>Support audits, inspections, and traceability documentation.</li></ul><p><strong>General Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Assist with unloading, loading, and internal stock transfers.</li><li>Operate basic warehouse equipment (pallet jacks, trolleys, etc.).</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned by supervisor.</li></ul>",
